Clone the git repos:

Then, you can clone the git repositories with:

git clone ssh://git1.ops.rhcloud.com/srv/git/li

And the Rack broker application with:

git clone ssh://git1.ops.rhcloud.com/srv/git/broker


Add Li Repo at /etc/yum.repos.d/li.repo.  Example in li/docs/li/.repo

yum install mcollective-common mcollective-client li rubygems rubygem-parseconfig rubygem-json rubygem-stomp rubygem-right_aws rubygem-aws rubygem-rake rubygem-rspec rubygem-cucumber

cp /etc/client.conf ~/.li
edit ~.li and point li_server your broker system
mkdir /etc/mcollective
cp li/backend/controller/test/etc/client.cfg /etc/mcollective/client.cfg

Example Usage:
rhc-create-domain -n <namespace> -l <rhlogin>
rhc-create-app -l <rhlogin> -a <appname> -r <Ex: /tmp/rhc/appname> -repo -t php-5.3.2 -b
You should now be able to browse to:  http://appname.userid.rhcloud.com
Now make a change under /tmp/rhc/appname
git commit -a -m "Test commit"
git push
The change should be seen at:  http://appname.namespace.rhcloud.com

Running Test Cases:
rake cuc_int sprint[1]
tail -f /tmp/rhc/cucumber.log (To see log output)
